# Security Policy

## Reporting a Vulnerability

If you believe you've discovered a security vulnerability in this repository, please follow the steps below to report it:

1. **Do not open an issue**: Please **do not open a public issue** for security vulnerabilities. We want to keep security issues private until a fix is available.

2. **Email us**: Send a detailed description of the vulnerability to [your-email@example.com]. We prefer to be contacted via email as it provides a secure way of sharing sensitive information.

3. **Provide the details**: Include the following information in your report:
   - A description of the issue.
   - Steps to reproduce (including any scripts or code to demonstrate the issue).
   - Any potential fixes or suggestions, if available.
   - The impact and severity of the issue.

4. **Response time**: We will acknowledge your report within 24-48 hours and work to address it promptly.

## Supported Versions

This project follows a [Security Patch Support Policy](https://opensource.guide/legal/). We provide security updates for the following versions:

- **Version X.Y.Z**: Supported
- **Version A.B.C**: Supported until YYYY-MM-DD

Please refer to the **releases** section to check the latest supported versions.

## Security Best Practices

To ensure the security of your environment, please follow these recommendations:
- **Update dependencies**: Regularly run `yarn audit` or `npm audit` to identify and fix vulnerabilities.
- **Use HTTPS**: Always use HTTPS for cloning and interacting with the repository.
- **Avoid using credentials in source code**: Never commit sensitive credentials (e.g., API keys, tokens) into the repository.
- **Run security lint the security advisories for the libraries you are using. We encourage you to use tools like [Dependabot](https://github.com/dependabot) to keep all dependencies up to date.

